{"lemma":"أَطٌّ","slug":"أَطٌّ","root":"#.ط.ط","root_slug":"_-ط-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ط-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n896","n897"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B7%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n896","headword_ar":"اَطَّ","root":"AT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTiyTN","text_ar":"اَطِيطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aT~N","text_ar":"اَطٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It produced, made, gave, emitted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uttered, a sound, noise, voice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cry;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) [and particularly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it creaked;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it moaned;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] said of a camel's saddle, (S, * K, [in the CK,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ajulu","text_ar":"الرَّجُلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put by mistake for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aHolu","text_ar":"الرَّحْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]) [and particularly of a new camel's saddle,] and the like, (K,) such as a [plaited or woven girth called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nisoE","text_ar":"نِسْع"},{"kind":"text","text":"and of everything of which the sound resembles that of a new camel's saddle, (TA,) and of a palm-trunk, and of a tree of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sidor","text_ar":"سِدْر"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S TA,) or of the kind called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saroH","text_ar":"سَرْح"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) and of a cane or reed on the occasion of its being straightened, [in which instance it is said to be tropical, but if so it is tropical in several other instances,] and of a bow, (TA,) and of the belly by reason of emptiness, (S,* TA,) and, in a trad. of Aboo-Dharr, (tropical:)  of heaven, or the sky, notwithstanding there being [really] no"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTiyT","text_ar":"اَطِيط"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this instance, for it is meant to denote [the presence of] multitude, and confirmation of the majesty of God. (TA.) [It is also said of other things, as will be shown by phrases here following, and by explanations of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTiyTN","text_ar":"اَطِيطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"below.] You also say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aT~ati","text_ar":"اَطَّتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA_ibilu","text_ar":"الاـِبِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor. as above, inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTiyTN","text_ar":"اَطِيطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camels moaned by reason of fatigue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uttering their yearning cry to their young,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) and sometimes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of fulness of their udders with milk."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A=tiyka maA A^aT~ati AlA_ibilu","text_ar":"لَا ا=تِيكَ مَا اَطَّتِ الاـِبِلُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not come to thee as long as camels utter cries"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moan"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of the heaviness of their loads."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA A^afoEalu *`lika maA A^aT~ati AlA_ibilu","text_ar":"لَا اَفْعَلُ ذٰلِكَ مَا اَطَّتِ الاـِبِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I will not do that ever."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA lanaA baEiyrN yay^iT~u","text_ar":"مَا لَنَا بَعِيرٌ يَيِطُّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We have not a camel that moans,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cries;"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"we have not any camel;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for the camel cannot but do so. (TA, from a trad.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTiyTN","text_ar":"اَطِيطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below.] And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aT~ato lahu raHimiY","text_ar":"اَطَّتْ لَهُ رَحِمِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My feeling of relationship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sympathy of blood,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became affected with tenderness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"compassion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became moved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pleaded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for him"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his favour"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (K, TA:) and hence ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alt~aA^aT~uTu","text_ar":"التَّاَطُّطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[inf. n. of the verb in the syn. phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taA^aT~aTato lahu raHimiY","text_ar":"تَاَطَّطَتْ لَهُ رَحِمِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Sgh, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aT~ato bika Alr~aHimu","text_ar":"اَطَّتْ بِكَ الرَّحِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The feeling of relationship,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sympathy of blood, pleaded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hath pleaded, in thee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inclined thee to favour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 765.) [See another ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAs~apN","text_ar":"حَاسَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n897","headword_ar":"اَطٌّ","root":"AT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTiyTN","text_ar":"اَطِيطٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", below."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A3%D8%B7/","headword_ar":"أط","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_3","lexicon_en":"Al-Khalīl b. Aḥmad al-Farāhīdī, Kitāb al-ʿAin (d. 786 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب العين للخليل بن أحمد الفراهيدي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=10698#137293","body_html":"<span>أط: أطيط: الأط والأطيط: صَوْتُ تَقَبُّضِ المَحامِل، أَطَّ أَطِيطأ، وكلُّ شيء ثقيل يُحمَلُ بَعْضُه على بَعضٍ يَئِطُّ. والأطاطُ: الصّياح. وأطيطُ الإبل: أَنينُها من ثِقَل الحِمْل، أو صوتُ هَزّة عليها.</span>"}]}}